
@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam classAttributeIconColor #000000

class Person {
  -personID: String
  -name: String
  -phoneNumber: String
  -keywords: List<String>
  -institutionCode: String
}

class ResearchInstitution {
  -institutionCode: String
  -name: String
  -address: String
}

class ScientificArticle {
  -doi: String
  -title: String
  -authors: List<Person>
  -authorPosition: Map<Person, Integer>
}

class PeerReviewedPaper extends ScientificArticle {
  -citationCount: Integer
  -reviewers: List<Person>
}

class TechnicalReport extends ScientificArticle {
  -publishingInstitutionCode: String
}

class Publisher {
  -name: String
}

class Journal {
  -publisherName: String
  -journalName: String
  -impactFactor: Double
  -subscribedBy: List<ResearchInstitution>
}

class Subscription {
  -researchInstitutionCode: String
  -journalName: String
  -publisherName: String
}

' Relationships
Person "1" *-- "0..*" ScientificArticle : author of
Person "1" *-- "0..*" ScientificArticle : reviewer of

ScientificArticle <|-- PeerReviewedPaper
ScientificArticle <|-- TechnicalReport

TechnicalReport o-- ResearchInstitution : published by

PeerReviewedPaper "1" *-- "0..*" Person : reviewed by

Publisher "1" *-- "0..*" Journal : publishes

Journal "1" *-- "0..*" ResearchInstitution : subscribed by

@enduml

### Explanation of Key Elements:
- **`Person`**: Represents a researcher with unique `personID`, works for an institution.
- **`ResearchInstitution`**: Identified by `institutionCode`, can have multiple researchers and publish technical reports.
- **`ScientificArticle`**: Base class for all articles, identified by `DOI`.
- **`PeerReviewedPaper`**: Subclass of `ScientificArticle`, includes citation count and reviewers.
- **`TechnicalReport`**: Subclass of `ScientificArticle`, always published by a single institution.
- **`Publisher`**: Identified by name, can have multiple journals.
- **`Journal`**: Has a name, impact factor, and is published by a publisher. Institutions can subscribe to it.
- **`Subscription`**: Links a research institution to a journal via its publisher.

